{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"WCbrUA0NYeimp+OBENybvU9N1wI=","kind":"plan","title":"Output UX Paper-Cut Sweep Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"oVooYmq7f2V9yhsY4/Ya9MsHw/s=","body":"# Output UX Paper-Cut Sweep Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Give `kref` a single human-readable presentation layer — a headered `list` with a colored tier column, a global `--json` flag, and consistent action confirmations — without changing any existing JSON shape.\n\n**Architecture:** A new pure `internal/render` package owns all human formatting (short ids, tier badges, the list table, the detail view, action lines). A thin `cmd/kref/output.go` seam (`emit`/`jsonMode`/`useColor`) routes each command to either `render` (default) or the frozen `writeJSON` (under `--json`). The root command gains one persistent `--json` flag; per-command `--json` flags are removed.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go 1.26.4, cobra, ginkgo/gomega, stdlib `unicode/utf8`/`strings`/`sort`, `golang.org/x/term` (already vendored, promoted to a direct dependency). No new modules.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-18-list-ux-papercuts-design.md`\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n- **Create** `internal/render/render.go` — `ShortID`, `Tier`, `List`, `Show`, `Action`, and unexported helpers (`pad`, tier glyph/color, sort).\n- **Create** `internal/render/render_suite_test.go` — ginkgo suite runner.\n- **Create** `internal/render/render_test.go` — render unit tests (no git repo needed).\n- **Create** `cmd/kref/output.go` — `emit`, `jsonMode`, `useColor`, and the `ingest` human summary helper.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/main.go` — root persistent `--json` flag.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/commands.go` — every command's output tail swaps to `emit`; `list` gains `--tier`; per-command `--json` flags removed.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` — JSON helper passes `--json`; new human-output specs.\n- **Modify** `go.mod` — `golang.org/x/term` indirect → direct (via `go mod tidy`).\n- **Modify** `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` — output examples + changelog entry.\n\nSequencing keeps the test suite green at every commit: the global `--json` flag and the test-helper migration land first (Task 4) so the existing JSON assertions opt into `--json` *before* any default flips.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: `render.ShortID` and `render.Tier`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/render/render.go`\n- Create: `internal/render/render_suite_test.go`\n- Create: `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the suite runner**\n\n`internal/render/render_suite_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage render_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n)\n\nfunc TestRender(t *testing.T) {\n\tRegisterFailHandler(Fail)\n\tRunSpecs(t, \"Render Suite\")\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing tests**\n\n`internal/render/render_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage render_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/render\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"ShortID\", func() {\n\tIt(\"truncates a long id to 12 chars\", func() {\n\t\tid := entity.Id(\"fdd23cc786c4ff4b732b38773a69a55cbc70aab1\")\n\t\tExpect(render.ShortID(id)).To(Equal(\"fdd23cc786c4\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"leaves a short id untouched\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(render.ShortID(entity.Id(\"abc\"))).To(Equal(\"abc\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Tier\", func() {\n\tIt(\"prefixes a glyph and omits ANSI when color is off\", func() {\n\t\tout := render.Tier(\"private\", false)\n\t\tExpect(out).To(Equal(\"● private\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"\\x1b[\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"wraps the badge in ANSI when color is on\", func() {\n\t\tout := render.Tier(\"private\", true)\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"● private\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(HavePrefix(\"\\x1b[\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(HaveSuffix(\"\\x1b[0m\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"falls back to a neutral glyph for an unknown tier\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(render.Tier(\"weird\", false)).To(Equal(\"• weird\"))\n\t\tExpect(strings.Contains(render.Tier(\"weird\", true), \"\\x1b[\")).To(BeFalse())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: render.ShortID` / `render.Tier` (package does not compile).\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Write the minimal implementation**\n\n`internal/render/render.go`:\n\n```go\n// Package render produces the human-readable presentation of kref entries.\n// It is pure: it depends only on internal/entry and the standard library, so\n// every function is unit-testable with a bytes.Buffer and an explicit color\n// flag. TTY detection and the --json decision live in cmd/kref, not here.\npackage render\n\nimport (\n\t\"unicode/utf8\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tansiReset  = \"\\x1b[0m\"\n\tansiRed    = \"\\x1b[31m\"\n\tansiYellow = \"\\x1b[33m\"\n\tansiGreen  = \"\\x1b[32m\"\n)\n\n// ShortID is the canonical 12-character entry id used by the listing and the\n// action confirmations. The detail view (Show) keeps the full id.\nfunc ShortID(id entity.Id) string {\n\ts := id.String()\n\tif len(s) \u003e 12 {\n\t\treturn s[:12]\n\t}\n\treturn s\n}\n\nfunc tierGlyph(tier string) string {\n\tswitch tier {\n\tcase string(entry.TierPrivate):\n\t\treturn \"●\"\n\tcase string(entry.TierPersonal):\n\t\treturn \"◐\"\n\tcase string(entry.TierShared):\n\t\treturn \"○\"\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"•\"\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc tierColor(tier string) string {\n\tswitch tier {\n\tcase string(entry.TierPrivate):\n\t\treturn ansiRed\n\tcase string(entry.TierPersonal):\n\t\treturn ansiYellow\n\tcase string(entry.TierShared):\n\t\treturn ansiGreen\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc tierPlain(tier string) string { return tierGlyph(tier) + \" \" + tier }\n\n// Tier renders a glyph-prefixed tier badge (\"● private\"). The glyph prints\n// regardless of color so the visibility signal survives NO_COLOR and piping.\nfunc Tier(tier string, color bool) string {\n\ts := tierPlain(tier)\n\tif color {\n\t\tif c := tierColor(tier); c != \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn c + s + ansiReset\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn s\n}\n\n// pad right-pads s with spaces to w columns, counting runes (the tier glyphs\n// are multi-byte, so byte-based padding would misalign).\nfunc pad(s string, w int) string {\n\tn := utf8.RuneCountInString(s)\n\tif n \u003e= w {\n\t\treturn s\n\t}\n\treturn s + spaces(w-n)\n}\n\nfunc spaces(n int) string {\n\tb := make([]byte, n)\n\tfor i := range b {\n\t\tb[i] = ' '\n\t}\n\treturn string(b)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS — `ok  github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/render`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_suite_test.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(render): tier badge and canonical short id\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: `render.List` — sorted, headered, colored table\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go`\n- Modify: `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go`:\n\n```go\nimport \"bytes\" // add to the existing import block\n\nfunc snap(tier, kind, status, title string, deleted bool) *entry.Snapshot {\n\treturn \u0026entry.Snapshot{\n\t\tID: entity.Id(strings.Repeat(\"a\", 40)), Tier: tier,\n\t\tKind: kind, Status: status, Title: title, Deleted: deleted,\n\t}\n}\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"List\", func() {\n\tIt(\"prints a header row and a tier column\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.List(\u0026b, []*entry.Snapshot{snap(\"shared\", \"spec\", \"open\", \"Auth\", false)}, false)\n\t\tout := b.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(MatchRegexp(`(?m)^TIER\\s+ID\\s+KIND\\s+STATUS\\s+TITLE$`))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"○ shared\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"Auth\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"sorts by tier rank then kind then title\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.List(\u0026b, []*entry.Snapshot{\n\t\t\tsnap(\"shared\", \"spec\", \"open\", \"Z\", false),\n\t\t\tsnap(\"private\", \"memory\", \"open\", \"A\", false),\n\t\t\tsnap(\"personal\", \"adr\", \"open\", \"M\", false),\n\t\t}, false)\n\t\tlines := strings.Split(strings.TrimSpace(b.String()), \"\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(lines[1]).To(ContainSubstring(\"private\"))\n\t\tExpect(lines[2]).To(ContainSubstring(\"personal\"))\n\t\tExpect(lines[3]).To(ContainSubstring(\"shared\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"marks deleted rows and prints a count footer\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.List(\u0026b, []*entry.Snapshot{snap(\"shared\", \"spec\", \"open\", \"T\", true)}, false)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"(deleted)\"))\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"1 entry\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"says 'no entries' for an empty list\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.List(\u0026b, nil, false)\n\t\tExpect(strings.TrimSpace(b.String())).To(Equal(\"no entries\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"emits ANSI only when color is on\", func() {\n\t\tvar plain, colored bytes.Buffer\n\t\titems := []*entry.Snapshot{snap(\"private\", \"memory\", \"open\", \"T\", false)}\n\t\trender.List(\u0026plain, items, false)\n\t\trender.List(\u0026colored, items, true)\n\t\tExpect(plain.String()).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"\\x1b[\"))\n\t\tExpect(colored.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"\\x1b[31m\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: render.List`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Write the minimal implementation**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render.go` (and add `\"fmt\"`, `\"io\"`, `\"sort\"` to its import block):\n\n```go\nfunc tierRank(tier string) int {\n\tswitch tier {\n\tcase string(entry.TierPrivate):\n\t\treturn 0\n\tcase string(entry.TierPersonal):\n\t\treturn 1\n\tcase string(entry.TierShared):\n\t\treturn 2\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn 3\n\t}\n}\n\n// List renders entries as a headered, tier-sorted table with a count footer.\n// Ordering is deterministic: tier rank → kind → title → id.\nfunc List(w io.Writer, items []*entry.Snapshot, color bool) {\n\tif len(items) == 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"no entries\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tsorted := make([]*entry.Snapshot, len(items))\n\tcopy(sorted, items)\n\tsort.SliceStable(sorted, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\ta, b := sorted[i], sorted[j]\n\t\tif ra, rb := tierRank(a.Tier), tierRank(b.Tier); ra != rb {\n\t\t\treturn ra \u003c rb\n\t\t}\n\t\tif a.Kind != b.Kind {\n\t\t\treturn a.Kind \u003c b.Kind\n\t\t}\n\t\tif a.Title != b.Title {\n\t\t\treturn a.Title \u003c b.Title\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn a.ID.String() \u003c b.ID.String()\n\t})\n\n\ttierW, kindW, statusW := len(\"TIER\"), len(\"KIND\"), len(\"STATUS\")\n\tfor _, it := range sorted {\n\t\tif n := utf8.RuneCountInString(tierPlain(it.Tier)); n \u003e tierW {\n\t\t\ttierW = n\n\t\t}\n\t\tif n := len(it.Kind); n \u003e kindW {\n\t\t\tkindW = n\n\t\t}\n\t\tif n := len(it.Status); n \u003e statusW {\n\t\t\tstatusW = n\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tconst idW = 12\n\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s  %s  %s  %s  %s\\n\",\n\t\tpad(\"TIER\", tierW), pad(\"ID\", idW), pad(\"KIND\", kindW), pad(\"STATUS\", statusW), \"TITLE\")\n\tfor _, it := range sorted {\n\t\ttitle := it.Title\n\t\tif it.Deleted {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  (deleted)\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s  %s  %s  %s  %s\\n\",\n\t\t\ttierCell(it.Tier, tierW, color),\n\t\t\tpad(ShortID(it.ID), idW),\n\t\t\tpad(it.Kind, kindW),\n\t\t\tpad(it.Status, statusW),\n\t\t\ttitle)\n\t}\n\tnoun := \"entries\"\n\tif len(sorted) == 1 {\n\t\tnoun = \"entry\"\n\t}\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"\\n%d %s\\n\", len(sorted), noun)\n}\n\n// tierCell pads the plain badge to width first (so column alignment is computed\n// on visible runes), then wraps the padded cell in color. tabwriter is avoided\n// because it counts ANSI escape bytes as visible width and would misalign.\nfunc tierCell(tier string, w int, color bool) string {\n\tcell := pad(tierPlain(tier), w)\n\tif color {\n\t\tif c := tierColor(tier); c != \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn c + cell + ansiReset\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn cell\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(render): sorted headered list table with tier column\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: `render.Show` and `render.Action`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go`\n- Modify: `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Show\", func() {\n\tIt(\"renders the full id and a colored tier word, no glyph\", func() {\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{\n\t\t\tID: entity.Id(\"fdd23cc786c4ff4b732b38773a69a55cbc70aab1\"),\n\t\t\tTier: \"private\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"Secret\",\n\t\t\tCreatedBy: \"Tester\", CreatedByEmail: \"t@t.io\", Body: \"body text\",\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.Show(\u0026b, s, false)\n\t\tout := b.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"fdd23cc786c4ff4b732b38773a69a55cbc70aab1\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"[private/open]\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"by Tester \u003ct@t.io\u003e\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"body text\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"●\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Action\", func() {\n\tIt(\"renders a one-line confirmation with verb, tier, short id, kind, title\", func() {\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{\n\t\t\tID: entity.Id(\"a5745cf9056545771011318e3c4179134ab5e624\"),\n\t\t\tTier: \"shared\", Kind: \"spec\", Title: \"Auth flow spec\",\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\trender.Action(\u0026b, \"added\", s, false)\n\t\tExpect(strings.TrimSpace(b.String())).To(Equal(`added ○ shared a5745cf90565  spec  \"Auth flow spec\"`))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: render.Show` / `render.Action`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Write the minimal implementation**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render.go`:\n\n```go\n// tierWord colors just the tier word (no glyph) for the [tier/status] badge in\n// the detail view, preserving the established Show format.\nfunc tierWord(tier string, color bool) string {\n\tif color {\n\t\tif c := tierColor(tier); c != \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn c + tier + ansiReset\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn tier\n}\n\n// Show renders the full detail view of one entry. The full id is intentional:\n// Show is the canonical reference surface, unlike the 12-char list/action ids.\nfunc Show(w io.Writer, snap *entry.Snapshot, color bool) {\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s [%s/%s] %s — by %s \u003c%s\u003e\\n\\n%s\\n\",\n\t\tsnap.ID, tierWord(snap.Tier, color), snap.Status, snap.Title,\n\t\tsnap.CreatedBy, snap.CreatedByEmail, snap.Body)\n}\n\n// Action renders a one-line confirmation, e.g.\n// `added ○ shared a5745cf90565  spec  \"Auth flow spec\"`.\nfunc Action(w io.Writer, verb string, snap *entry.Snapshot, color bool) {\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s %s %s  %s  %q\\n\",\n\t\tverb, Tier(snap.Tier, color), ShortID(snap.ID), snap.Kind, snap.Title)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(render): detail view and action confirmation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Output seam + global `--json` (suite stays green)\n\nThis task adds the routing seam and the persistent flag, and migrates the CLI\ntest helper to request `--json` — *before* any default flips — so the existing\nJSON assertions keep passing.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `cmd/kref/output.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go:25` (after the `--dir` flag registration)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (the JSON-capturing helper)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Create the output seam**\n\n`cmd/kref/output.go`:\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"os\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n\t\"golang.org/x/term\"\n)\n\n// jsonMode reports whether the inherited persistent --json flag is set.\nfunc jsonMode(cmd *cobra.Command) bool {\n\tv, _ := cmd.Flags().GetBool(\"json\")\n\treturn v\n}\n\n// useColor enables ANSI color only for human output to an interactive\n// terminal, and never when NO_COLOR is set. Detection keys off the real stdout\n// fd; under `go test` (and pipes) it is not a terminal, so output is plain and\n// deterministic.\nfunc useColor(cmd *cobra.Command) bool {\n\tif jsonMode(cmd) || os.Getenv(\"NO_COLOR\") != \"\" {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\treturn term.IsTerminal(int(os.Stdout.Fd()))\n}\n\n// emit routes a command's output: frozen JSON under --json, otherwise the\n// human closure with a resolved color flag.\nfunc emit(cmd *cobra.Command, human func(w io.Writer, color bool), jsonValue any) error {\n\tif jsonMode(cmd) {\n\t\treturn writeJSON(cmd, jsonValue)\n\t}\n\thuman(cmd.OutOrStdout(), useColor(cmd))\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Register the persistent flag**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, immediately after the existing\n`root.PersistentFlags().StringVar(\u0026dir, \"dir\", \".\", \"repository directory\")`\nline, add:\n\n```go\n\troot.PersistentFlags().Bool(\"json\", false, \"machine-readable JSON output\")\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Migrate the CLI test JSON helper**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`, the helper that runs a command and captures JSON\noutput (the functions at lines ~16-21 and ~27-33 that build args, call\n`cmd.SetArgs(args)` and unmarshal `out`) must append `--json` to the args so\nthe frozen JSON path is exercised. Add `args = append(args, \"--json\")` (or\ninclude `\"--json\"` in the constructed slice) in each JSON-capturing helper.\nLeave any helper that asserts human/plain text alone.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Verify the suite still passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS — no command uses `emit` yet, so defaults are unchanged; the\nhelper change is a harmless no-op flag today and prepares for the flips.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/output.go cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(cli): global --json flag and output routing seam\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Migrate `list` — header, tier column, `--tier` filter\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go:178-217` (`newListCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (new human-output specs)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI specs**\n\nAdd to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (inside the existing top-level `Describe`, using the\nsuite's existing buffer-run pattern — build a fresh root via `newRootCmd()`,\n`SetOut(\u0026buf)`, `SetArgs([...])`, `Execute()`):\n\n```go\nIt(\"list prints a header and a tier column by default\", func() {\n\tdir := initStore() // existing helper that inits a store and returns its dir\n\taddEntry(dir, \"spec\", \"Auth flow spec\", \"shared\") // existing add helper\n\tvar buf bytes.Buffer\n\tcmd := newRootCmd()\n\tcmd.SetOut(\u0026buf)\n\tcmd.SetArgs([]string{\"--dir\", dir, \"list\"})\n\tExpect(cmd.Execute()).To(Succeed())\n\tExpect(buf.String()).To(MatchRegexp(`(?m)^TIER\\s+ID\\s+KIND\\s+STATUS\\s+TITLE$`))\n\tEx